# code-context — copy to .env and adjust. Overrides the defaults in src/code_context/config.py.

# Postgres (derived index in schema code.*).
# Dev = the isolated pgvector container (infra/docker-compose.yml, host port 5433).
# Prod: point this at the shared ai-life instance.
CODE_CONTEXT_DB_DSN=postgresql://dev:dev@localhost:5433/code_context
CODE_CONTEXT_DB_SCHEMA=code

# Ollama inference engine. Dev: the Windows box; prod: the Mac.
CODE_CONTEXT_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
CODE_CONTEXT_EMBED_MODEL=nomic-embed-text
CODE_CONTEXT_EMBED_DIM=768

# Index-time enrichment (C-4): the analyzers that write LLM notes over parser facts.
# Prod default = qwen3-coder:30b (on the Mac). Dev on the Windows box: use the small local model.
CODE_CONTEXT_NOTES_MODEL=qwen3:8b
# A leaf note sees one class' facts — RAG-first, no giant window. Raise only if notes truncate.
# CODE_CONTEXT_NOTES_NUM_CTX=8192
# Per-note analyzer timeout. Raise when driving a big model on slow (CPU) hardware.
# CODE_CONTEXT_NOTES_TIMEOUT_S=180
# Rollup tier (C-4b, dir→module→project). It has its OWN default in code (it is NOT derived from
# the notes model) — switch both when you change analyzers.
CODE_CONTEXT_ROLLUP_MODEL=qwen3:8b
# A rollup prompt aggregates every child note of a directory (the module/project tiers are the
# largest), so it gets its own window + timeout — the leaf budget truncates and times these out.
# CODE_CONTEXT_ROLLUP_NUM_CTX=32768
# CODE_CONTEXT_ROLLUP_TIMEOUT_S=900
# Cloud escalation (C-4): prefix ANY analyzer model with "anthropic:" and llm.py routes that call
# to the Messages API instead of Ollama — the roadmap's strong rollup tier for cross-file
# reasoning. Needs `uv sync --extra cloud` and a key the SDK can find (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in the
# environment, or an `ant auth login` profile — code-context never reads or stores the key).
# It costs real money per directory, so it is opt-in and the defaults above stay local.
# CODE_CONTEXT_ROLLUP_MODEL=anthropic:claude-opus-4-8
# Output ceiling for a cloud call — sized for adaptive thinking, not for the few-sentence note.
# CODE_CONTEXT_CLOUD_MAX_TOKENS=16000
#
# OpenAI-dialect tier: prefix ANY analyzer model with "openai:" and the call goes to the gateway
# below as /chat/completions instead of Ollama. This is the path for a COMPANY LLM — one URL, a
# key, usually several models behind it. No extra to install (plain httpx).
#   CODE_CONTEXT_NOTES_MODEL=openai:<the model your gateway exposes>
#   CODE_CONTEXT_ROLLUP_MODEL=openai:<same or a stronger one>
# The base URL must include the version prefix. NEVER commit the real one — this repo is public
# and an internal hostname identifies an employer as surely as a name does (see the scrub-identity
# skill and .private-terms).
# CODE_CONTEXT_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://llm.example.internal/v1
# The key is read from the ENVIRONMENT ONLY and is never held in the settings object (which is one
# print() away from a log). Put it in your shell/.env, never in a committed file:
# CODE_CONTEXT_OPENAI_API_KEY=
#
# THE SHELL READS THE SAME TWO VALUES. opencode reaches the gateway through its own provider block
# (`@ai-sdk/openai-compatible`, baseURL + apiKey "{env:CODE_CONTEXT_OPENAI_API_KEY}") — written by
# scripts/work-win.ps1 -GatewayUrl … -Model …, see README §Use it on a work machine. One gateway,
# one key, two consumers: this analyzer tier and the shell. Set the key as a real ENVIRONMENT
# variable (setx / your profile), not only here — opencode is a separate process and never reads
# this file.
# Thinking models burn the whole budget reasoning about a two-sentence note. This sends
# "reasoning_effort":"none" — the ONLY thing that works over an OpenAI /v1 endpoint (the qwen
# "/no_think" tag does not; ai-life paid to learn that). Measured here on qwen3:8b over Ollama's
# own /v1: 33.5s -> 3.7s for the same one-word answer, which also came back clean instead of
# trailing a stray "/think". Off by default: a gateway that rejects unknown body fields would fail
# every call, so turn it on once you've seen yours accept it.
# CODE_CONTEXT_OPENAI_SUPPRESS_THINKING=false
# Filenames that mark a directory as a build "module" (→ kind='module'); else 'directory'.
# JSON list. Widen it for non-Java stacks (e.g. add package.json / pyproject.toml).
# CODE_CONTEXT_MODULE_MARKERS=["pom.xml","build.gradle","build.gradle.kts"]
# Redirect md notes off a stand-in repo (e.g. indexing ../ai-life) into a scratch tree.
# Empty/unset → written in-repo at <repo>/.code-context/notes (Layer 1, git-tracked in real targets).
# CODE_CONTEXT_NOTES_ROOT=

# --- Confluence REST sync (decision B) ------------------------------------------------------
# The wiki's site URL as you see it in a browser. NEVER COMMIT THE REAL ONE: an internal hostname
# identifies an employer as surely as a name does (scrub-identity / .private-terms).
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL=https://wiki.example.internal
# The REST root under that site. Data Center/Server: rest/api. Cloud: wiki/rest/api.
# Explicit rather than sniffed — a wrong guess looks exactly like an auth failure.
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_API_PATH=rest/api
# Set for CLOUD ONLY — it switches the client to Basic (email + API token). Leave empty for a Data
# Center Personal Access Token, which is sent as a Bearer.
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=
# The token is read from the ENVIRONMENT ONLY and is never a settings field (one print() from a
# log — same rule as the OpenAI key):
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_TOKEN=
# 'view' = macros rendered (code macro -> <pre>, table macro -> <table>), the shape the D-1 parser
# was written against. 'storage' is the raw editor format; macros then arrive as
# <ac:structured-macro> the parser cannot see into.
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_BODY_FORMAT=view
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_PAGE_LIMIT=50
# CODE_CONTEXT_CONFLUENCE_TIMEOUT_S=60

# Docs ingest (C-3). A section bigger than this is split into parts that keep the same heading path
# — one giant wiki table would otherwise be a fragment too large to embed usefully.
# CODE_CONTEXT_DOCS_MAX_CHARS=4000
# Where a converted binary document lands (.docx → md, D-6). Empty/unset → <docs>/.code-context/md.
# The markdown is the Layer-1 record — the .docx is neither greppable nor diffable, so without it
# the only readable form of the document is rows in the index. Set this to keep the export
# directory pristine (e.g. a read-only mount of the corpus).
# CODE_CONTEXT_DOCS_MD_ROOT=

# Retrieval: the target budget a single tool call returns (~8–20k tokens of context).
# CODE_CONTEXT_SEARCH_DEFAULT_LIMIT=10
# The repo every tool scopes to when the caller passes none. One index can hold several projects
# (plus their docs corpora) and an unscoped query mixes them — a wrong answer, not a wide one.
# Set this for a session pinned to one project; leave empty only for a deliberate cross-repo index.
# THE VALUE IS THE REPO'S *NAME*, NOT ITS PATH — `dev index <path>` stores the directory's leaf
# name (e.g. C:\src\my-monorepo → "my-monorepo") and the scope filter is an exact compare, so a
# path here matches nothing and every tool comes back empty while looking configured.
# CODE_CONTEXT_DEFAULT_REPO=

# Lifecycle signal to ai-life (C-6a) — the coder-side half of ai-life's LC-4 model swap. OFF by
# default: without it this repo is standalone and never talks to ai-life at all. Turn it on only
# when both contours share one Mac + one Ollama, because then the ~48 GB GPU ceiling is real: we
# signal "coder-active" and WAIT for ai-life to finish evicting its 32B model BEFORE loading ours,
# and on the way back we unload ours, confirm it is gone, then signal "normal".
# CODE_CONTEXT_LIFECYCLE_ENABLED=false
# ai-life's llm-gateway (it owns the model profile). Default = the same-Mac case; ai-life's compose
# publishes the gateway on host port 8081.
# CODE_CONTEXT_LIFECYCLE_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:8081
# Wait budget for ai-life's confirmation — it has to unload a 32B model, so this is not an HTTP
# round trip. Exceeding it FAILS the analyzer call rather than loading over the ceiling.
# CODE_CONTEXT_LIFECYCLE_SIGNAL_TIMEOUT_S=180
# Wait budget for OUR model to leave Ollama before ai-life is told it may restore its big one.
# CODE_CONTEXT_LIFECYCLE_UNLOAD_TIMEOUT_S=120
# Release the shared engine after this long with no analyzer call (the next call re-acquires);
# 0 disables the idle timer, leaving release to the end of the run.
# CODE_CONTEXT_LIFECYCLE_IDLE_TTL_S=900

# Observability (architecture.md §Observability). Events go to STDERR as JSON Lines — stdout is the
# MCP protocol channel, and a collector (Filebeat/Promtail) ships the stream to Elasticsearch/Kibana.
# INFO = run start/finish + counts + warnings; DEBUG adds per-node events (enrich.note, rollup.note,
# llm.generate) with timings. The level changes how MUCH is logged, never WHETHER payloads are:
# prompts, class bodies and note text are customer source code and are never logged, at any level.
# CODE_CONTEXT_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# CODE_CONTEXT_LOG_FORMAT=json                   # json = JSON Lines (ship it); text = human-readable
